E. Scott Beattie  Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President, Elizabeth Arden, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships58$4,905,941As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. E. Scott Beattie has been the Chief Executive Officer of Elizabeth Arden, Inc. since March 1998 and as its President since August 2006. Mr. Beattie serves as an Executive Vice President of Bedford Capital Limited. He served as President of Elizabeth Arden Inc. from April 1997 to March 2003, as Chief Operating Officer from April 1997 to March 1998 and Vice Chairman and Assistant Secretary of Elizabeth Arden Inc. from November 1995 to April 1997. Mr. Beattie served ... as an Executive Vice President of Bedford Capital Corporation from March 1995 to March 1998 and Vice President of Bedford from September 1989 to March 1995. Prior to co-founding Bedford, he served as Vice President and Director of Mergers & Acquisitions of Merrill Lynch Inc., where he specialized in management buyouts and divestitures. Mr. Beattie served as also a Manager of Andersen Consulting, specializing in the design and implementation of enterprise resource planning systems. Since the inception of FFI in 1992, he has been actively involved in FFI's management and development, including the recruitment of members of senior management, brand acquisitions and financings, business strategy development and implementation, customer and supplier relationships and other operating activities. Mr. Beattie served as Chairman of Elizabeth Arden, Inc. since April 2000. He has been Non-Executive Vice-Chairman of Revlon, Inc. since September 7, 2016. He has been Director of Elizabeth Arden Inc. since January 1995. He serves as Director of Bedford Capital Corporation and BCC Advisors Inc. He serves as Director of the Cosmetic, Toiletry & Fragrance Association and a Member of the Advisory Board of the Ivey Business School. He also serves as a Director of the Fragrance Foundation Inc. He served as a Director of ObjectVideo, Inc. since December 16, 2004. Mr. Beattie earned a Master of Business Administration in 1986 and a Bachelor of Arts degree in Honors Business Administration in 1981, both from the University of Western Ontario, Ivey School of Business.Read Full Background




